msgctxt "0001"
msgid "See you later."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid "Sure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid "Not a chance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0004"
msgid "Actually..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "near00"
msgid "*snore*... *snore*..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "near01"
msgid "Mmmm..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk00"
msgid "<1.so>..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You're a traveler, aren't you?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Then listen up!<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You see those three trees up on top of\n"
"that snowy mountain there?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I found a small letter stuck between the\n"
"pages of this old book at my house...\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>It said, \"When the three summit trees\n"
"become one, turn your back to them and\n"
"head toward the sea.\n"
"A trial encased in stone awaits you\n"
"there.\" I don't know what that means!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: sound
#. 6: set_colour (red)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But maybe it means we have to head to\n"
"<2.se_co>Afromsia Coast<3.re_co>, <4.pa>which is just east of\n"
"those three trees on the mountain! \n"
"<5.so>For the \"trial <6.se_co>encased in stone<7.re_co>...\" bit,\n"
"I wonder if you get some kind of treasure\n"
"for doing that..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid "<1.so>Mornin'."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk06"
msgid "<1.so>Good day."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk07"
msgid "<1.so>Evenin'."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid "<1.so>Ahhh, Hateno..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I need some time to relax...<2.pa> We can talk\n"
"later on."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid "<1.so>Are you a traveler?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh? <2.pa>That <3.se_co>blue flame<4.re_co>... Is that the same\n"
"as the one Purah has?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You'd better hurry and take that\n"
"<2.se_co>blue flame <3.re_co>over to Purah's."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid "<1.so>Oh, dear...<2.pa> What a shame."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: choice
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid "<1.so>Oh, you're back? <2.pa>Got a second to chat?<3.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid "<1.so>Zzz...zzz..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Did you happen to find the treasure...<2.pa>\n"
"by any chance?\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>I guess it probably wasn't fair of me to\n"
"expect you to do all of the exploring\n"
"and adventuring...\n"
"But maybe we could split the treasure\n"
"seventy-thirty or something like that?<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Beyond the three summit trees...<2.pa> Did you\n"
"ever make it over <3.se_co>Afromsia Coast<4.re_co>?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hmm... <2.pa>You look like a traveler type \n"
"to me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>There's something I've been waiting to\n"
"show to an adventurous soul...<2.pa>but I \n"
"can't do it when it's raining like this."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk21"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Ah, I'm just kidding!\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>I'm plenty satisfied with what I have in\n"
"my life as it is.<3.pa> The key is to always live\n"
"within your means, you know?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk22"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But I have a child! I can't just go off\n"
"on a journey across the mountains...\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>But you can do that, right?! <3.pa>You'd be\n"
"great at that! <4.pa>Go on! Head out there and\n"
"bring us back that treasure!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: single_choice
msgctxt "talk23"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Eh?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>What's wrong? Why the long face?<3.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: sound
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk25"
msgid ""
"<1.so>A shrine?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>That's it?<3.pa> No treasure?\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<4.so>Well...thanks for looking into it. <5.pa>I guess\n"
"I'm kinda relieved.<6.pa> But I was really\n"
"hoping there'd be some treasure..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (blue)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk26"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Beyond the three summit trees...<2.pa>\n"
"there was only a <3.se_co>shrine<4.re_co>, huh?\n"
"\n"
"We have our very own shrine here\n"
"in the village, so I'm not so impressed..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk27"
msgid "<1.so>In that case, follow me for a minute."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: set_colour (blue)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk28"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That <2.se_co>blue flame<3.re_co>...<4.pa> Wait, isn't that the\n"
"<5.se_co>lab director<6.re_co>'s..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk29"
msgid ""
"<1.so>You should hurry up and take that\n"
"<2.se_co>blue flame <3.re_co>up to the <4.se_co>lab director<5.re_co>."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk30"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Then there's something I want to show\n"
"you. <2.pa>No questions, just follow me."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk31"
msgid "<1.so>You're a traveler if e'er I saw one!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: choice
msgctxt "talk32"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Thanks for waitin', <2.pa>traveler!\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>Why don't you take a moment and lemme\n"
"tug on your tunic for a second...speakin'\n"
"figuratively, of course.<4.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk33"
msgid "<1.so>All right, see ya later! "
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk34"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm flattered that a young man like\n"
"yourself wants to chew the fat,<2.pa>\n"
"but these bones need their sleep..."
msgstr ""

